Statistics can be grouped and/or filtered by days, months, sites, blocks and countries.
The response contains two fields:
**1) `data`** - which, in turn, consists of a statistics field - `result`
and a field of total values for grouping - `total_result`
**2) `names`** - contains a transcript of the names of some entities, if grouping by country is used.
** Usage algorithm:**
1. Specify the correct date range using `filters[date_from]` and `filters[date_to]`.
2. Specify the value of the grouping `groups[0]`, which will determine the display of statistics
(in the context of sites or blocks, or countries or dates, etc.).
3. Use the filters `filters[entity name]` to specify for which specific entity you want to display statistics
(for example `filters[site_id]: 13588 & filters[month]: 2020-09`).
Please note that only one value can be specified for each filter type!
4. Specify the sorting using two fields:
1) `order_by[0][column]` (by the parameter specified in the grouping or by the general parameter of statistics
- the number of impressions, the number of clicks, etc.) and
2) `order_by[0][direction]` (sorting direction: desc / asc).
5. Limit the amount of data displayed by using "cut-off" filters for the specified entity
by adding `_in` to its name at the end. You can specify multiple filter values for each parameter,
for example: `filters[block_id_in][0]: 1265665 & filters[block_id_in][1]: 1265556`' operationId: webmasterStats parameters: - $ref: '#/components/parameters/queryFiltersDateFrom' - $ref: '#/components/parameters/queryFiltersDateTo' - $ref: '#/components/parameters/queryFiltersSiteIdIn' - $ref: '#/components/parameters/queryFiltersBlockIdIn' - $ref: '#/components/parameters/queryFiltersCountryCodeIn' - $ref: '#/components/parameters/queryFiltersDeviceTypeIdIn' - $ref: '#/components/parameters/queryFiltersBlockUuidIn' - name: 'filters[date]' in: query description: 'The filter specifies for which specific (ONE) date the statistics should be displayed.' schema: type: string example: '2020-09-22' - name: 'filters[month]' in: query description: 'The filter specifies for which specific (ONE) month statistics should be displayed.' schema: type: string example: 2020-09 - name: 'filters[block_id]' in: query description: 'The filter specifies for which specific (ONE) block statistics should be displayed.' schema: type: integer example: 121212 - name: 'filters[site_id]' in: query description: 'The filter specifies for which specific (ONE) site you want to display statistics.' schema: type: integer example: 11111 - name: 'filters[country_code]' in: query description: 'The filter indicates for which specific (ONE) country display statistics.' schema: type: string example: NL - name: 'filters[referrer_domain]' in: query description: 'The filter specifies which domain from the referrer to display statistics for.' schema: type: string example: wwww.google.com - name: 'filters[referrer_domain_in][]' in: query description: 'The filter specifies which domains from the referrer to display statistics for. (You can specify several values: `filters[referral_domain_in][0]=www.google.com & filters[referrer_domain_in][1]=www.yoursite.com`)' schema: type: string example: www.google.com - name: 'groups[0]' in: query description: 'The following grouping options are available:
